  • Method Details

    • of

      public static <T> FilteredIterator<T> of(Iterator<T> iterator, Predicate<? super T> predicate)
      Creates a FilteredIterator instance from the provided Iterator.

      This FilteredIterator contains all elements of iterator such that for each element e, predicate.test(e) is true

      If an element e in the underlying Iterator exists such that predicate.test(e) is false, the element is ignored and is not removable with Iterator.remove(), retrievable with Iterator.next() or counted as an element with Iterator.hasNext().
      Type Parameters:
      T - The type of the Iterator and the resulting FilteredIterator
      Parameters:
      iterator - The Iterator to create a FilteredIterator instance from.
      predicate - The Predicate that determines whether an item is included.
